  "ShortLegislativeSummaryEn": "<div>The Library of Parliament does not prepare Legislative Summaries for appropriation bills, ways and means bills and borrowing-authority bills. The following is a short summary:<br/><br/>On 24 March 2026, the President of the Treasury Board introduced Bill C-23, An Act for granting to Her Majesty certain sums of money for the federal public administration for the financial year ending March 31, 2026, in the House of Commons and it was given first reading.<br/><br/>Bill C-23 (Appropriation Act No. 4, 2025-26) received Royal Assent on 26 March 2026 and authorizes payments to defray certain expenses of the public service of Canada, not otherwise provided for, for the financial year ending 31 March 2026. The Act provides for the sum of $5,408,955,628 to be appropriated from the Consolidated Revenue Fund to be used the public service of Canada. The Act came into force on Royal Assent.</div>",
  "ShortLegislativeSummaryFr": "<div>La Bibliothèque du Parlement ne prépare pas de Résumés législatifs pour les projets de lois portant affectation de crédits, les projets de loi de voies et moyens et les projets de loi portant pouvoir d'emprunt. Ce qui suit est un court résumé :<br/><br/>Le 24 mars 2026, le président du Conseil du Trésor a déposé le projet de loi C-23, Loi portant octroi à Sa Majesté de crédits pour l'administration publique fédérale pendant l'exercice se terminant le 31 mars 2026, à la Chambre des communes en première lecture.<br/><br/>Projet de loi C-23 (Loi de crédits no 4 pour 2025-2026) a reçu la sanction royale le 26 mars 2026 et autorise les versements au titre de certaines dépenses de l’administration publique du Canada, auxquelles il n’est pas pourvu par ailleurs, pour l’exercice financier se terminant le 31 mars 2026. La Loi prévoit la somme de 5?408?955?628 $ à prélever sur le Trésor public aux fins de l’administration publique fédérale. La Loi est entrée en vigueur dès la sanction royale.</div>",
  "ShortLegislativeSummary": "<div>The Library of Parliament does not prepare Legislative Summaries for appropriation bills, ways and means bills and borrowing-authority bills. The following is a short summary:<br/><br/>On 24 March 2026, the President of the Treasury Board introduced Bill C-23, An Act for granting to Her Majesty certain sums of money for the federal public administration for the financial year ending March 31, 2026, in the House of Commons and it was given first reading.<br/><br/>Bill C-23 (Appropriation Act No. 4, 2025-26) received Royal Assent on 26 March 2026 and authorizes payments to defray certain expenses of the public service of Canada, not otherwise provided for, for the financial year ending 31 March 2026. The Act provides for the sum of $5,408,955,628 to be appropriated from the Consolidated Revenue Fund to be used the public service of Canada. The Act came into force on Royal Assent.</div>",
